Interface StateStorage<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    IndexedSet

    public interface StateStorage<T>
    Interface for storing a set of objects of type T. Typically used for storing states during reachability.

        list - An empty ArrayList in which to store the result.

      • buildSortingPermutation

        int[] buildSortingPermutation()
        Build sort permutation. Assuming this was built as a sorted set, this returns a permutation (integer array) mapping current indices to new indices under the sorting order.
